EAR will therefore be:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{EAR}&=\left(1+\frac{\text{q}}{\text{m}}\right)^{\text{m}}-1\\[15pt]
&=\left(1+0.3333\right)^{52}-1\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{313,916,515.69\%}
\end{aligned}$$

APR will be:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{APR}&=\text{q} \times \text{t}\\[10pt]
&=0.3333 \times52\\[10pt]

&=\boxed{1,733.33\%}
\end{aligned}$$

The annual percentage rate can be calculated using the following formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{APR} &=\text{Period}\times\text{Interest rate}
\end{aligned}$$
